(Lucrécia)[24] My housing condition is inhumane, and one of our group’s biggest ambitions is to improve it, so we spend more time [with our children]. (Xico) The better we are economically the more we can contribute to the school and society. (Madalena) I want to work as a domestic servant because I think it’s an easy job. Helping someone to clean the house and cook for them is not difficult. All you have to do is to love the work. WHAT RELATIONS? Some people realised that there was no need for their children to continue schooling at this stage – they can get a job and start earning for themselves. The premature withdrawal of children from school is deeply entrenched among the groups.
